# PRISM4D Binding Site Visualization
# Generated by prism-nhs
# Industry-standard pocket visualization

# Setup
set bgColor white
lighting soft

# Load your structure (adjust path as needed)
# open 1crn.topology.pdb
# cartoon
# color #1 gray80

# ========== Site 1 (ActiveSite) [DRUGGABLE] ==========
# Pocket 1 lining residues
name pocket1_lining #1/A:29,/A:12,/A:25,/A:31,/A:26,/A:8,/A:30,/A:28,/A:3,/A:11,/A:27,/A:9,/A:15,/A:4,/A:24,/A:13,/A:32,/A:22,/A:1,/A:16,/A:2,/A:7,/A:33,/A:10,/A:23,/A:14,/A:5,/A:43
show pocket1_lining atoms
style pocket1_lining stick
color #1/A:31,/A:30,/A:32,/A:33,/A:43 magenta
surface pocket1_lining
transparency pocket1_lining 70
color pocket1_lining slate gray
marker #101 position 8.997,9.809,6.894 color red radius 1.0
2dlabels text "Pocket 1 (57% druggable) *" xpos 0.02 ypos 0.95 color black size 14

# ========== Color Legend ==========
# Magenta = Catalytic residues (GLU, ASP, HIS, SER, CYS, LYS)
# Forest Green = Aromatic residues (PHE, TYR, TRP)
# Gold = Hydrophobic residues (ALA, VAL, LEU, ILE, MET, PRO)
# Slate surface = Pocket cavity
# Red marker = Druggable site centroid
# Gray marker = Non-druggable site centroid

# ========== Usage ==========
# To view pocket: view pocket1_lining
# To hide surface: hide pocket1_lining surface
# To show H-bonds: hbonds pocket1_lining
